  "summary": "Malicious code in @emilgroup/setting-sdk (npm)",
  "details": "\n---\n_-= Per source details. Do not edit below this line.=-_\n\n## Source: amazon-inspector (679e8996c56ffd334a5fd610afb087430e91e54ef7371e70ba8ce6170b3b9cf9)\nThe package @emilgroup/setting-sdk was found to contain malicious code.\n\n## Source: google-open-source-security (8024c6ab9e2a90120288605aead40496c0059184b47bec681c39acf7e54c90af)\nThis package was compromised by the CanisterWorm campaign by the TeamPCP\nthreat actor. The malicious payload establishes persistence as user systemd\nservice and places a backdoor on the infected host. The malware will also\nharvest npm credentials and can autonomously spread.\n",
